Our interpretation of the GNU Affero General Public License version 3
(Quoted words refer to terms defined by the license itself.)

1. You must always provide the source code, copyright notice, and license information of adonis-debugbar whenever you "convey" any part of it, whether modified or unmodified.

2. adonis-debugbar was developed as a standalone library and therefore without knowledge of your application or work. Because of this:

   a) adonis-debugbar should generally not be considered a work "based on" your application solely because it is used within it.

   b) If you have not modified, adapted, or extended adonis-debugbar itself, then your own application should not become subject to the AGPL merely by using it as part of an aggregate work.

   c) If you modify, adapt, or extend adonis-debugbar itself, then those modifications must remain licensed under the AGPLv3 when conveyed.

3. If you use adonis-debugbar over a network in a way covered by the AGPLv3, users interacting with it must be able to access the corresponding source code as required by the license.

We hope this interpretation aligns with the goals and freedoms intended by the AGPLv3 while helping developers feel comfortable adopting and contributing to adonis-debugbar.

